The paper presents a new method for selecting an initial solution for the k-modes algorithm, which is a clustering algorithm commonly used in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also compares the proposed method with other initialisations on benchmark datasets and newly generated artificial datasets, which suggests a focus on evaluation and experimentation, making cs.DM (Data Mining) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method on low-density data, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
